# GALAXY EMPIRE — Master Game Design Document
> Version 0.1 | Status: Planning Phase
> Last Updated: June 2026

---

## 🎯 Core Concept
A hybrid FPS/RTS open-world space sandbox combining:
- **Empyrion** — seamless planet-to-space travel, first-person gameplay, planetary exploration
- **Avorion** — deep faction economies, procedural galaxy, sector-based space structure
- **Bannerlord** — seamless FPS ↔ RTS camera switch during combat

No single game has combined all three. This is the gap we fill.

---

## 🔁 Core Gameplay Loop (Every 30 Seconds)
> Build your empire. Explore POIs. Fight or trade. Expand.

1. Gather resources (mine, extract, loot POIs)
2. Feed factories → produce goods → generate credits
3. Build new structures / ships
4. Expand to new planet cells, planets, or systems
5. Fight or diplomacy with NPC factions
6. Repeat at larger scale

---

## 🌌 World Structure

### Galaxy Scale
- Procedurally generated galaxy of solar systems
- Travel between systems requires **hyperjump**
- Each system contains: planets, moons, asteroid fields, space stations, faction territory

### Space (Avorion Model)
- Space divided into **sectors** — each a self-contained zone
- Each sector has unique resources, factions, POIs, dangers
- Sectors stream in/out as the player travels

### Planets (Streaming Cell Model)
- Each planet is a sphere divided into a **hex cell grid**
- Only 1–3 cells active at a time — streams silently as player moves
- Feels open world, runs like a managed zone
- Flying in from space lands you in the cell your trajectory targets
- Flying out transitions seamlessly back to space (no load screen)
- Cell = battlefield boundary when in RTS mode

### Planet Types & Biomes
| Planet Type | Example Biomes | Key Resources |
|-------------|---------------|---------------|
| Temperate | Forest, Grassland, Swamp | Wood, Iron, Food crops |
| Arid | Desert, Badlands, Canyons | Silicon, Rare minerals |
| Lava | Volcanic, Ash fields | Rare metals, Thermal energy |
| Ocean | Open sea, Coastal, Deep | Hydrogen, Exotic compounds |
| Ice | Tundra, Glaciers, Caves | Crystals, Frozen gases |
| Barren | Rocky, Craters | Basic ore, Salvage |

- Flora and fauna match planet type and biome
- Resource deposits vary by biome within a planet
- NPC spawning tied to biome type

