## 🏭 Economy System (Avorion Model)

### Tiers
1. **Raw Extraction** — Mining rigs, drills, harvesters
2. **Processing** — Smelters, refineries, sawmills
3. **Manufacturing** — Component factories, weapons plants, ship parts
4. **End Products** — Ships, structures, weapons, trade goods

### Flow
- Factories consume inputs and produce outputs in real time
- Supply/demand shifts based on player AND NPC faction activity
- Players can fill supply gaps or crash markets by flooding them
- Automated trade fleets run supply lines between stations

### Player Economy Tools
- Found factories and mines
- Set up automated trade routes
- Use spies/scouts to read faction economy status
- Blockade faction trade lanes to weaken their military

---

## 🤝 Faction System

### Behavior
- Factions are **actively expansionist** — they build new bases, factories, and ships
- Expansion is funded by their own economy (hurt economy = weaker military)
- They patrol and defend high-value worlds (life-bearing, resource-rich)
- They fight each other, not just the player
- They send scouts before claiming new territory

### Faction Types (Examples)
- Military/Aggressive — large fleet, less economy
- Economic/Trade — large economy, small military, buys defense
- Balanced — moderate both
- Pirate — raids everyone, no territory building

### Diplomacy
- Trade agreements, alliances, tributes, wars
- Reputation built through combat support, commerce, or missions
- High reputation = discounts, intel sharing, allied defense

---

## 🏗️ Building System

### Two Modes
1. **Modular Block Building** — Custom design block by block (ships, bases, factories)
2. **Blueprint Structures** — Premade deployable buildings for fast empire expansion

### Structure Types
| Category | Examples |
|----------|----------|
| Bases | Starter Base, Command Center, Defense Outpost |
| Factories | Smelter, Component Factory, Shipyard, Food Plant |
| Extraction | Planet Mine, Space Mining Rig, Gas Harvester |
| Military | Turret Tower, Barracks, Launch Pad |
| Logistics | Trade Depot, Storage Hub, Fuel Station |

---

## 🚀 Ships & Vehicles

- Ships built modularly or from blueprints
- Classes: Fighter, Freighter, Capital Ship, Mining Vessel
- Can be crewed by NPCs and automated
- Piloted in FPS or commanded in RTS
- Seamless transition: land ship on planet, exit on foot, re-enter ship

---

## 🗺️ POIs (Points of Interest)

- Scattered across every planet cell and space sector
- Types: Abandoned bases, enemy outposts, derelict ships, resource caches
- Loot tiers: Common, Rare, Very Rare, Ultra Rare
- Some POIs are faction-owned and guarded
- Neutral POIs are open to anyone — race factions to them

---

## 🏆 Victory Conditions

### Sandbox (Default)
- No win condition — play indefinitely
- Build the biggest empire possible

### Optional Victory Settings
- **Domination** — Control X% of the galaxy
- **Economic** — Reach a credit/production threshold
- **Elimination** — Destroy all rival factions
- **Exploration** — Discover and chart the full galaxy

